One could easily emulate a FDS (before MMC5) but of course it'll require a flexible system due to the FDS's odd mapping. There are quite a few old Taiwanese FDS hardware emulators which are basically RAM adapters which play cartridges and swap sides via a pushbutton.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=20">kyuusaku</a> — Mon Dec 06, 2004 8:28 pm</p><hr />
