<div class="quotetitle">SgtBowhack wrote:</div><div class="quotecontent"><br />IIRC, the disk is completely stored on the RAM adapter before it's run<br /></div><br />FDS disk: 64 KB per side.<br />RAM adapter: 32 KB EWRAM, 8 KB VRAM.<br />Many programs came on two disks.<br /><br />But then, you could emulate the FDS by rewriting the BIOS to speak ATA PIO rather than speaking FDS low-level control signals.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=9">tepples</a> — Mon Dec 06, 2004 5:35 pm</p><hr />
